rever running to catch up to it!\n\n- Ryan Graudin, Invictus\n|\nWho hears music, feels his solitudePeopled at once.\n\n- Robert Browning, The complete poetical works of Browning\n|\nIf death blew a trumpet each time he was coming, there would be no one to greet him on arrival.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nDaniel 12:3 '...and those who turn the many to righteousness will shine the stars forever.\n\n- Craig W. Dressler, Hafren: A Fantasy for the Young at Heart\n|\nOn what rests the hope of the republic? One country, one language, one flag!\n\n- Alexander\n|\nI'll love you, dear, I'll love you till China and Africa meet and the river jumps over the mountain and the salmon sing in the street.\n\n- W.\n|\nEl sabio puede cambiar de opinión. El necio, nunca.\n\n- Immanuel\n|\nYou are given a life, a death. Understand both while living, and before dying. Or you'd have wasted a life, a death.\n\n- Fakeer\n|\nSometimes in the quest of searching the stars in others eyes, we fall into the never ending pit of darkness.\n\n- Akshay\n|\nLife. All this. Why do they need to make us do this? Why do they treat us like we're their slaves?''Power.''Power isn't real. It's just a word.\n\n- Pierce Brown, Red Rising\n|\nHappiness is an awareness—a blissful perception, not in ownership or in material possessions.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI wanted to shout down to him, to warn him that he was giving flowers to a monster, but I did not.\n\n- Neil Gaiman, The Ocean at the End of the Lane\n|\nHold the thoughts, know the thoughts and you realize the thoughts have slowed showing breaks and gaps, be the witness to them and you shall be meditating\n\n- Maitreya\n|\nReality wasn't as important as people made it out to be; to Jude it was simply the physical state in which he found himself, an environment he had limited control over.\n\n- Gemma Malley, The Resistance\n|\nI'll quote the truth wherever I find it, thank you.\n\n- Richard Bach, Illusions: The Adventures of a Reluctant Messiah\n|\nHave you noticed,' said John, 'how countries call theirs 'sovereign nuclear deterrents,' but call the other countries' ones 'weapons of mass destruction'?\n\n- David Mitchell, Ghostwritten\n|\nLove permeates all and energizes life.Even evil has love. If not, she is dead.\n\n- Toba Beta, My Ancestor Was an Ancient Astronaut\n|\nWe are not slaves of the past, nor servants of the present, but masters of the future.\n\n- A.J. Darkholme, Rise of the Morningstar\n|\nSeperti apakah Anda? Menurut saya, paling tidak Anda adalah apa yang Anda tulis.\n\n- Helvy\n|\nYou can't hate your best friend for taking opportunities he'd been given. That would be the worst sort of hate, wouldn't it? Because it would mean you hate yourself, too.\n\n- Craig Davidson, Cataract City\n|\nWhat was that you gave me to eat?' Winter panicked.A Filler Crisp,' Clover said, his eyes seventy percent concerned and thirty percent mischievous.\n\n- Obert Skye, Leven Thumps and the Gateway to Foo\n|\nNo matter how much we try to keep things in order, life seems determined to scatter Legos under our bare feet.\n\n- Sammy\n|\nValue of life depends not on your possessions, but on your donation.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nA well hit golf shot is a feeling that goes up the shaft, right through your hands and into your heart.\n\n- Ben\n|\nThose thinking Why, When, Where, Who are information providers; the one thinking “HOW” is the leader in solving the problem.\n\n- Vikrmn, Guru with Guitar\n|\nThe sun can shine, and it can burn. You can shine your love with a softer power than the sun.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThe first step in any Journey, Is the belief that the road will open up in front of you even if you cant see it....\n\n- Meg\n|\nWinning isn’t everything, but losing isn’t anything.\n\n- Charles M. Schulz, The Complete Peanuts, Vol. 9: 1967-1968\n|\nBecause failure works double time, to get success, work triple time.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nMy lasting impression of Truman Capote is that he was a terribly gentle, terribly sensitive, and terribly sad m